rComments: 3 Tests worth 20% each and a final worth 40% She has a very thick accent and is very disorganized with her lecture. She gets off topic during lectureS way too many times. Also, her tests are also super hard with plenty of short / long answers. This course would be easier if there were tutorials every week. All in all, wish I never took this course!

Lorenza was amazing! There's 5 tests each worth 10% every couple of weeks and then the final exam is 40%. The tests are about 2 pages of translating and analyzing latin, but the content is really straightforward and she marks REALLY easy! Class participation is worth 10% so just make sure you do your homework and answer when she calls on you
